rows.description: Maintains application systems that have completed the development stage and are running in the daily operations of the firm; provides production support for all internally and externally developed systems and applications, ensuring that service is delivered in an uninterrupted manner.

Responsible for technical planning within the technology organization; architects interpret business strategy into target state Architecture utilizing patterns, cost models, and industry best practices.
Cybersecurity protects the firm's people, clients, and information assets ensuring the safety and soundness of the firm's business operations.

Responsible for the design, development, testing , integration, operation and support of infrastructure services that meet stated business requirements and adhere to coding best practices and architecture standards.

Builds strong working relationships with clients and businesses to effectively provide end-to-end infrastructure service related to production assurance, connectivity services and service improvement. Level 2 and Level 3 support.

Primarily responsible for the overall strategic organizational management for IT teams; most experienced members who spend over 50% of their time on organizational management and skill sets are fungible across all Job Families.

Technology Control Officers ensure the robust control, security and resiliency of the firm's computing environment, protect customer and employee confidential information, and comply with regulatory requirements globally.
